Get ready to start the game!

Thank you for reading the instructions. Get ready start with the 40 rounds of this game.

If you need to take a break, feel free to take one after the end of a round, before continuing to the next one.

Remember, the more money the spider gets, the bigger your bonus will be!

Press space to begin.


(If, at any point, the space key does not take you to the next page, click once on the text and try again.)

response.Q0: I focused on revealing the end nodes, as I didn't want to spend to much money on revealing nodes that weren't end nodes. Once I identified the most valuable end node (usually around 80) I went to it without wasting money on nodes between the starting point and the end node.
response.Q1: Yes. At the beginning I spent money trying to find the optimal way to an end node, which meant I spent money on nodes that weren't end nodes. But over time I realized it was better to spend money only on the end nodes and go to them as soon as I revealed one with a high value (usually around 80). This way I minimized the cost.
response.Q2: I think it was a bit difficult to improve my performance because the game is very dependent on luck. Either you're lucky and quickly identify a high value end node, thus decreasing the cost of revealing nodes, or you spend too much money on revealing nodes, and once you do find a high value end node you have already spent too much.

response.Q1: I haven't participated in a Web of Cash HIT before. This was my first time.
